on a diverse range of methods including material from the French colonial archives, aerial photographs, imagery from Landsat satellites, a review of project reports and interviews with key informants. I show the importance of cash crops in landscape change, in particular booms in the cultivation
of maize. I also show that economic and political factors operating at a range of spatial levels have been critical in stimulating the expansion of these crops.},
